  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003eNestled in a serene, forested enclave of Portland, Oregon, the \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/shedarchitecture/p/DCW_YBdATbH/?img_index=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMori House\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e merges mid-century modern architecture with contemporary minimalist sensibilities. Originally designed in 1963 by Saul Zaik, a revered figure in Pacific Northwest architecture, this home has been thoughtfully reimagined by \u003ca href=\"https://www.shedbuilt.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSHED Architecture \u0026amp; Design\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e to meet the aesthetic and functional needs of its new owners: a young family with a passion for design.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=563166\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-563166\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2-810x532.jpg\" alt=\"A modern, dark wood house surrounded by trees, featuring large windows and a wraparound deck.\" width=\"810\" height=\"532\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2-810x532.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2-800x525.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2-768x504.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2-385x252.jpg 385w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-2.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSet on a sloped, wooded lot, the Mori House makes a striking yet understated statement. The property includes a detached garage and studio, along with a teahouse pavilion, accessible via elevated decks. These elements, framed by towering trees, create a peaceful retreat that prioritizes connection with the natural environment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=563167\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-563167\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3-810x1126.jpg\" alt=\"Modern house with large glass windows surrounded by dense green trees, showcasing an interior with wooden furniture and artwork.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1126\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3-810x1126.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3-800x1112.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3-768x1067.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3-1105x1536.jpg 1105w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House-Portland-SHED-Architecture-3.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eZaik’s original blueprint was a celebration of mid-century modern design, marked by clear geometries and the use of organic materials. The current remodel extends this vision, weaving in Japanese-inspired minimalism. SHED’s approach preserves the house’s architectural integrity while enhancing light, space, and the fluidity between indoors and outdoors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=563168\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-563168\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/11/Mori-House